  <h1>
   gpu_get_texrepeat
  </h1>
  With this function you can check to see whether texture repeating is enabled (returns
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  ) or not (returns
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  ). For more information on texture repeating, see the function
  <a href="gpu_set_texrepeat.htm">
   <span>
    gpu_set_texrepeat()
   </span>
  </a>
  .
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">gpu_get_texrepeat();
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Boolean
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if gpu_get_texrepeat()
{
    gpu_set_texrepeat(false);
}
else
{
    gpu_set_texrepeat(true);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code checks to see if texture repeating is on or off and switches it accordingly.
 </body>
